Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy was used to examine doped CeO2 as a mixed-conducting electrode material for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: THE CHARACTERIZATION OF DOPED CEO2 ELECTRODES IN SOLID OXIDE FUEL-CELLS

Sentencas: Sintered oxide disks with a composition of Ce0.9M0.1O2 (M = Co, Ni, and Mn) were used at 1000-degrees-C in two types of cell: Pt/Ce0.9M0.1O2/Pt and Ce0.9M).1O2/9% Y2O3-ZrO2/Pt.
Titulo: THE CHARACTERIZATION OF DOPED CEO2 ELECTRODES IN SOLID OXIDE FUEL-CELLS

Sentencas: The impedance spectra for the cell containing two platinum electrodes exhibited three depressed semicircles, with the highest-frequency semicircle corresponding to the bulk oxide.
Titulo: THE CHARACTERIZATION OF DOPED CEO2 ELECTRODES IN SOLID OXIDE FUEL-CELLS

Sentencas: Oxygen reduction on Ni- and Co-CeO2 electrodes in air was studied as a function of voltage using the Y2O3-ZrO2 cell.
Titulo: THE CHARACTERIZATION OF DOPED CEO2 ELECTRODES IN SOLID OXIDE FUEL-CELLS

Sentencas: The spectra in this case exhibited two distinct semicircles, with the high-frequency relaxation being ascribed to O2 reduction at the cathode and the other to mass transport of O2 or O2-.
Titulo: THE CHARACTERIZATION OF DOPED CEO2 ELECTRODES IN SOLID OXIDE FUEL-CELLS
